//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_director_invest}

NOTE: This operation invests a
{rbtr_director}
{giam_service_account}
into the
{rbtgi_depot_project}.
The
{rbtr_governor}
mints the SA, generates its credential key, and writes the RBRA bytes to the assay output slot.
The operation is identity-parameterized: a required identity folio (param1) is supplied by the operator; the SA account name is composed as `${RBCC_account_director}-<identity>`.
Idempotent establish: a pre-existing SA is not drift — its identity (email, `uniqueId`) and IAM bindings are preserved and only the credential key is rotated; an absent SA is created first. Either path ends with exactly one fresh USER_MANAGED key and the role's bindings in place.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_governor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Compose
{rbtr_director}
Service Account Identity*:
.. {rbbc_require}
identity folio (param1) is non-empty
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_ACCOUNT_NAME»` as `${RBCC_account_director}-<identity>` (operator-supplied identity composing the account name)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` as `«DIRECTOR_ACCOUNT_NAME»@${RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID}.iam.gserviceaccount.com` (depot project ID derived from `(RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER)` at regime kindle time)

//axhos_step
. *Preflight: Detect Existing Service Account*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/get[iam.serviceAccounts.get] for `projects/-/serviceAccounts/«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«SA_EXISTS»` true on HTTP 200 (the SA and its bindings are kept; only the key is rotated below), false on HTTP 404 (the SA is created below)
.. {rbbc_fatal}
on any other HTTP code — an indeterminate preflight is not a re-key signal

//axhos_step
. *Create
{rbtr_director}
Service Account* (when `«SA_EXISTS»` is false):
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/create[iam.serviceAccounts.create] with:
... accountId: `«DIRECTOR_ACCOUNT_NAME»`
... displayName: `Recipe Bottle Director (<identity>)`
... description: `Create/destroy container images for <identity>`
... project:
{rbtgi_depot_project}
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_UNIQUE_ID»` from response `.uniqueId` field
.. NOTE: Skipped when `«SA_EXISTS»` is true — the identity is preserved and `«DIRECTOR_UNIQUE_ID»` is read from the preflight response instead.

//axhos_step
. *Verify Service Account Propagation* (when `«SA_EXISTS»` is false):
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/get[iam.serviceAccounts.get] for `projects/-/serviceAccounts/«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»`
.. {rbbc_poll}
with backoff until HTTP 200 (newly-created SA may not be immediately resolvable by email)
.. NOTE: Poll must use the email address, not the numeric ID. The email-based lookup path has independent propagation from the UID-based path, and subsequent steps (keys.list, keys.create) all use the email address. Polling by UID can succeed while the email path still returns 404.
.. NOTE: Skipped when `«SA_EXISTS»` is true — a pre-existing SA is already propagated.
.. {rbbc_require}
service account accessible by email

//axhos_step
. *Blunt-Kill Existing Keys*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/list[serviceAccounts.keys.list] for `«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»`
.. Retry up to `RBGC_SA_KEY_CREATE_RETRY_MAX` times on HTTP 404 with `RBGC_SA_KEY_CREATE_RETRY_DELAY_SEC` delay between attempts
.. NOTE: Keys subresource read-path may lag SA email-path readiness — the SA GET probe (previous step) can return 200 while `keys.list` on the same email immediately returns 404, observed as a non-monotonic 200→200→404 flap on freshly-minted depots. The 404 confirms `keys.list` returned no state, making retry safe. Shares budget with step 7 keys.create — same underlying physics (subresource visibility after parent creation). See `Memos/memo-20260514-pristine-gauntlet-iam-flap.md` for transcript evidence and <<rbscip_trade_study>> for the doctrinal pattern.
.. {rbbc_store}
`«EXISTING_KEYS»` as the `.name` of every `.keys[]` entry with `keyType: USER_MANAGED`
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/delete[serviceAccounts.keys.delete] for each `«EXISTING_KEYS»` entry
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 OR HTTP 404 (key already gone — idempotent) for each delete
.. NOTE: Re-key rotates the Key lifecycle only — the SA and its IAM bindings are untouched. Deleting every user-managed key before minting guarantees exactly one fresh key when this operation completes (the blunt kill). This replaces the former fail-loud "manual cleanup via Console" abort.

//axhos_step
. *Generate Service Account Key*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/create[serviceAccounts.keys.create] for `«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with:
... privateKeyType: `TYPE_GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS_FILE`
.. Retry up to `RBGC_SA_KEY_CREATE_RETRY_MAX` times on HTTP 404 with `RBGC_SA_KEY_CREATE_RETRY_DELAY_SEC` delay between attempts
.. NOTE: SA read operations (GET by email, keys.list) may succeed while keys.create POST returns 404 "does not exist" due to write-path propagation delay. Google link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/service-accounts-create[documents]: "you might need to wait 60 seconds or more before you use the service account." The 404 confirms no key was created, making retry safe. See <<rbscig_iam_grant_contracts>>.
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»` from response `.privateKeyData` field
.. {rbtoe_rbra_generate}
converts `«DIRECTOR_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»` to `«DIRECTOR_RBRA_FILE»`

//axhos_step
. *Get Depot Project Number*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/get[projects.get] for
{rbtgi_depot_project}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PROJECT_NUMBER»` from `.projectNumber` field

//axhos_step
. *Grant Project-Level Permissions*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_project} for
{rbtgi_depot_project}
.. Add `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with roles:
... `roles/cloudbuild.builds.editor` (submit and manage builds)
... `roles/viewer` (read project resources)
... `roles/cloudbuild.workerPoolUser` (use private pool for vouch `builds.create`)
.. Policy version: 3
.. {rbbc_require}
IAM policy update successful

//axhos_step
. *Grant
{rbtr_mason}
Impersonation*:
.. NOTE:
{rbtr_director}
submits builds that execute as
{rbtr_mason}.
This requires `serviceAccountUser` permission on
{rbtr_mason}.
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_sa} on
{rbtr_mason}
service account
.. Add `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with `roles/iam.serviceAccountUser`
.. {rbbc_require}
IAM binding successful

//axhos_step
. *Grant
{rbtgi_build_bucket}
Access*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_bucket} on
{rbtgi_build_bucket}
.. Add `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with roles:
... `roles/storage.objectCreator` (upload sources)
... `roles/storage.objectViewer` (verify uploads)
.. {rbbc_require}
bucket IAM update successful

//axhos_step
. *Grant
{rbtgi_repository}
Admin Access*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories/getIamPolicy[repositories.getIamPolicy] via HTTP GET with `options.requestedPolicyVersion=3` query parameter
.. NOTE:
{gar_registry}
proto specifies GET for `getIamPolicy` with no `additional_bindings` for POST. Using POST fails intermittently with HTTP 404 (transcoding layer rejection, not missing repository). See <<rbscig_iam_grant_contracts>>.
.. NOTE: Resource-scope IAM cache lag — on a freshly-levied depot, the governor's `roles/owner` grant may not yet have reached the AR-resource-scope IAM cache, even though it has reached project-scope and SA-scope caches.  This surfaces as HTTP 403 on the very first `getIamPolicy` call.  The grant harness absorbs this via class C tolerance (HTTP 403 with empty body-glob, time-bounded against `RBGC_PROPAGATION_DEADLINE_SEC`) — see <<rbscig_iam_grant_contracts>> propagation catalog.  Real propagation succeeds within budget; real denial waits the budget and fails cleanly.
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 — 404 means repository does not exist (real error, not empty policy)
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories/setIamPolicy[repositories.setIamPolicy] for
{rbtgi_repository}
.. *Complete policy write*: Add ALL expected bindings to the read policy, regardless of what the read returned:
... `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with `roles/artifactregistry.repoAdmin` — Director manages images
... `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/artifactregistry.writer` — Mason pushes images at build time
.. NOTE: Same complete-policy-write pattern as the secret IAM step. Prevents stale read from overwriting Mason's writer binding set by
{rbtgo_depot_levy}.
.. {rbbc_require}
repository IAM set with all expected bindings

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtgi_rbra_file}
. *Deliver Credential to Assay Output Slot*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_RBRA_FILE»` RBRA bytes to the assay output slot via the producer-output discipline (the orphan's `${BURD_OUTPUT_DIR}` credential write retires)

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution invests director service account `«DIRECTOR_ACCOUNT_NAME»` with build management permissions, generates its credential key, and writes the RBRA file to the assay output slot.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_director_divest}

NOTE: This operation tears down a
{rbtr_director}
{giam_service_account}
from the
{rbtgi_depot_project}.
The
{rbtr_governor}
synthesizes the SA email from the supplied identity folio, *revokes the SA's own IAM bindings across every scope it was granted*, then issues a REST DELETE against the IAM API, and opportunistically removes the production RBRA file if its `client_email` matches the synthesized email.
Revoking the live member before the delete is what keeps the binding leak closed: a member removed while still live leaves no `deleted:...?uid=` ghost, whereas deleting the SA first would have GCP retag its bindings as unbounded tombstones.
A required identity folio (param1) is supplied by the operator; the SA email is composed as `${RBCC_account_director}-<identity>@${RBGD_SA_EMAIL_FULL}`.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_governor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Synthesize Service Account Email*:
.. {rbbc_require}
identity folio (param1) is non-empty
.. {rbbc_store}
`«SA_EMAIL»` as `${RBCC_account_director}-<identity>@${RBGD_SA_EMAIL_FULL}` (composed from the role prefix and the operator-supplied identity)

//axhos_step
. *Revoke
{rbtr_director}
IAM Bindings*:
.. NOTE: Run before the DELETE so each live member is removed while the SA still exists — no `deleted:...?uid=` tombstone is minted on any resource. Mirrors exactly the bindings granted by {rbtgo_director_invest}; the {rbtr_mason} `roles/artifactregistry.writer` binding is Mason's, not the director's, and is left intact. See the member-removal contract in <<rbscig_iam_grant_contracts>>.
.. Remove `serviceAccount:«SA_EMAIL»` from the
{rbtgi_depot_project}
IAM policy, roles:
... `roles/cloudbuild.builds.editor`
... `roles/viewer`
... `roles/cloudbuild.workerPoolUser`
.. Remove `serviceAccount:«SA_EMAIL»` with `roles/iam.serviceAccountUser` from the
{rbtr_mason}
service account IAM policy
.. Remove `serviceAccount:«SA_EMAIL»` with `roles/artifactregistry.repoAdmin` from the
{rbtgi_repository}
IAM policy
.. Policy version: 3; a binding left with no members is pruned
.. {rbbc_fatal}
on revoke failure — teardown is fail-loud: a non-OK policy status or an HTTP 409 etag conflict (single-writer invariant) aborts the divest before the SA is deleted; the operator reruns. The {rbtgi_repository} and {rbtr_mason} revokes presume those standing resources exist (they outlive director SAs); a missing resource there surfaces only during a full depot teardown.
.. NOTE: Idempotent — removing an absent member is a no-op, so a re-divest revokes cleanly without error.

//axhos_step
. *Divest Director Service Account*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/delete[iam.projects.serviceAccounts.delete] with:
... method: `DELETE`
... endpoint: `https://iam.googleapis.com/v1/projects/{rbtgi_depot_project}/serviceAccounts/«SA_EMAIL»`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «GOVERNOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response OR HTTP 404 (already divested)
.. {rbbc_warn}
if HTTP 404: "Service account not found (already divested)"

//axhos_step
. *Confirm Deletion Propagated*:
.. {rbbc_poll}
the SA GET endpoint until it returns HTTP 404 for `RBGC_GONE_CONFIRM_STREAK` consecutive observations, confirming the
{giam_service_account}
is durably gone. A delete-accepted response precedes propagation, and the post-delete read path flaps 404→200 across replicas (see <<rbscip_trade_study>>), so a single 404 is not durable proof — an immediately following same-name
{rbtgo_director_invest}
would otherwise race a still-visible account. Any intervening non-404 resets the streak.
.. NOTE: skipped when the DELETE returned HTTP 404 — the account was already absent, so there is nothing to wait for
.. {rbbc_require}
`RBGC_GONE_CONFIRM_STREAK` consecutive HTTP 404s within the eventual-consistency deadline

//axhos_step
. *Opportunistic RBRA Cleanup*:
.. If the role's RBRA file exists at
{rbrr_director_rbra_file},
source it and read `RBRA_CLIENT_EMAIL`
.. If `RBRA_CLIENT_EMAIL` equals `«SA_EMAIL»`, remove the file
.. NOTE: The removal is conditional — if the installed RBRA's `client_email` does not match the divested `«SA_EMAIL»` (e.g., a different identity is currently installed), the file is left in place. No fatal error is raised when the file is absent or non-matching.

//axhos_step
. *Display Result*:
.. {rbbc_show}
single-line success naming `«SA_EMAIL»` and confirming the
{rbtr_director}
{giam_service_account}
was divested, or a notice that it was already absent

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution revokes the
{rbtr_director}
{giam_service_account}'s IAM bindings across every scope it held (project,
{rbtr_mason},
{rbtgi_repository}) and then removes it from
{rbtgi_depot_project}, leaving no `deleted:` ghost on any policy.
If the installed RBRA at
{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
matches the divested identity, it is also removed; otherwise it is left intact.
A 404 response from the cloud DELETE is accepted as success — the
{giam_service_account}
is absent either way.
Proceed to
{rbtgo_director_invest}
to re-issue a fresh
{rbtr_director}
{giam_service_account}
when needed.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_retriever_invest}

NOTE: This operation invests a
{rbtr_retriever}
{giam_service_account}
into the
{rbtgi_depot_project}
with read-only
{rbtgi_repository}
access.
The
{rbtr_governor}
mints the SA, generates its credential key, and writes the RBRA bytes to the assay output slot.
The operation is identity-parameterized: a required identity folio (param1) is supplied by the operator; the SA account name is composed as `${RBCC_account_retriever}-<identity>`.
Idempotent establish: a pre-existing SA is not drift — its identity (email, `uniqueId`) and IAM bindings are preserved and only the credential key is rotated; an absent SA is created first. Either path ends with exactly one fresh USER_MANAGED key and the role's bindings in place.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_governor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Compose
{rbtr_retriever}
Service Account Identity*:
.. {rbbc_require}
identity folio (param1) is non-empty
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RETRIEVER_ACCOUNT_NAME»` as `${RBCC_account_retriever}-<identity>` (operator-supplied identity composing the account name)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` as `«RETRIEVER_ACCOUNT_NAME»@${RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID}.iam.gserviceaccount.com`
.. NOTE: `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID` is derived from `(RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER)` at regime kindle time; no operator-supplied project ID field is referenced.

//axhos_step
. *Preflight: Detect Existing Service Account*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/get[iam.serviceAccounts.get] for `projects/-/serviceAccounts/«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«SA_EXISTS»` true on HTTP 200 (the SA and its bindings are kept; only the key is rotated below), false on HTTP 404 (the SA is created below)
.. {rbbc_fatal}
on any other HTTP code — an indeterminate preflight is not a re-key signal

//axhos_step
. *Create
{rbtr_retriever}
Service Account* (when `«SA_EXISTS»` is false):
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/create[iam.serviceAccounts.create] with:
... accountId: `«RETRIEVER_ACCOUNT_NAME»`
... displayName: `Recipe Bottle Retriever (<identity>)`
... description: `Read-only access to Google Artifact Registry - identity: <identity>`
... project:
{rbtgi_depot_project}
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RETRIEVER_UNIQUE_ID»` from response `.uniqueId` field
.. NOTE: Skipped when `«SA_EXISTS»` is true — the identity is preserved and `«RETRIEVER_UNIQUE_ID»` is read from the preflight response instead.

//axhos_step
. *Verify Service Account Propagation* (when `«SA_EXISTS»` is false):
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/get[iam.serviceAccounts.get] for `projects/-/serviceAccounts/«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»`
.. {rbbc_poll}
with backoff until HTTP 200 (newly-created SA may not be immediately resolvable by email)
.. NOTE: Poll must use the email address, not the numeric ID. The email-based lookup path has independent propagation from the UID-based path, and subsequent steps (keys.list, keys.create) all use the email address. Polling by UID can succeed while the email path still returns 404.
.. NOTE: Skipped when `«SA_EXISTS»` is true — a pre-existing SA is already propagated.
.. {rbbc_require}
service account accessible by email

//axhos_step
. *Blunt-Kill Existing Keys*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/list[serviceAccounts.keys.list] for `«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»`
.. Retry up to `RBGC_SA_KEY_CREATE_RETRY_MAX` times on HTTP 404 with `RBGC_SA_KEY_CREATE_RETRY_DELAY_SEC` delay between attempts
.. NOTE: Keys subresource read-path may lag SA email-path readiness — the SA GET probe (previous step) can return 200 while `keys.list` on the same email immediately returns 404, observed as a non-monotonic 200→200→404 flap on freshly-minted depots. The 404 confirms `keys.list` returned no state, making retry safe. Shares budget with step 7 keys.create — same underlying physics (subresource visibility after parent creation). See `Memos/memo-20260514-pristine-gauntlet-iam-flap.md` for transcript evidence and <<rbscip_trade_study>> for the doctrinal pattern.
.. {rbbc_store}
`«EXISTING_KEYS»` as the `.name` of every `.keys[]` entry with `keyType: USER_MANAGED`
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/delete[serviceAccounts.keys.delete] for each `«EXISTING_KEYS»` entry
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 OR HTTP 404 (key already gone — idempotent) for each delete
.. NOTE: Re-key rotates the Key lifecycle only — the SA and its IAM bindings are untouched. Deleting every user-managed key before minting guarantees exactly one fresh key when this operation completes (the blunt kill). This replaces the former fail-loud "manual cleanup via Console" abort.

//axhos_step
. *Generate Service Account Key*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/create[serviceAccounts.keys.create] for `«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` with:
... privateKeyType: `TYPE_GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS_FILE`
.. Retry up to `RBGC_SA_KEY_CREATE_RETRY_MAX` times on HTTP 404 with `RBGC_SA_KEY_CREATE_RETRY_DELAY_SEC` delay between attempts
.. NOTE: SA read operations (GET by email, keys.list) may succeed while keys.create POST returns 404 "does not exist" due to write-path propagation delay. Google link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/service-accounts-create[documents]: "you might need to wait 60 seconds or more before you use the service account." The 404 confirms no key was created, making retry safe. See <<rbscig_iam_grant_contracts>>.
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RETRIEVER_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»` from response `.privateKeyData` field
.. {rbtoe_rbra_generate}
converts `«RETRIEVER_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»` to `«RETRIEVER_RBRA_FILE»`

//axhos_step
. *Grant
{rbtgi_repository}
Read Access*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_project} for
{rbtgi_depot_project}
.. Add `serviceAccount:«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` with role:
... `roles/artifactregistry.reader` (read-only access to all Artifact Registry repositories)
.. Policy version: 3
.. {rbbc_require}
IAM policy update successful
.. NOTE: This grant is project-scope (against the depot project's IAM policy), not resource-scope.  Project-scope IAM caches absorb the governor's `roles/owner` propagation effectively instantly, so this step does not need class C (HTTP 403) propagation tolerance — only class A/B (HTTP 400 member-visibility) coverage from the grant harness.  See <<rbscig_iam_grant_contracts>> propagation catalog.

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtgi_rbra_file}
. *Deliver Credential to Assay Output Slot*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RETRIEVER_RBRA_FILE»` RBRA bytes to the assay output slot via the producer-output discipline (the orphan's `${BURD_OUTPUT_DIR}` credential write retires)

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution invests retriever service account `«RETRIEVER_ACCOUNT_NAME»` with read-only Artifact Registry access, generates its credential key, and delivers the RBRA credential bytes to the assay output slot.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_director_roster}

NOTE: This operation rosters
{rbtr_director}
{giam_service_account_s}
in the
{rbtgi_depot_project}
via per-SA fact-file emission.
Read-only observation: lists all SAs, filters to director-prefixed emails, and emits one fact per discovered SA via
{buf_write_fact_multi}
against the `RBCC_fact_ext_roster_director` extension constant.
Fact value is the full SA email; `file_root` is the bare identity extracted from the email.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_governor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` from the resulting access token

//axhos_step
. *List service accounts*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/list[iam.projects.serviceAccounts.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `https://iam.googleapis.com/v1/projects/{rbtgi_depot_project}/serviceAccounts`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «GOVERNOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ACCOUNTS»` from response `.accounts[]` array

//axhos_step
. *Filter to director service accounts*:
.. From `«ACCOUNTS»`, read the `.email` field of each entry and test whether it matches `^${RBCC_account_director}-(.+)@${RBGD_SA_EMAIL_FULL}$`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_EMAILS»` — the matching emails; per-role observation per BBAAQ contract

//axhos_step
. *Emit Fact Per Discovered {rbtr_director}*:
.. For each `«SA_EMAIL»` in `«DIRECTOR_EMAILS»`:
... {rbbc_store}
`«IDENTITY»` from the regex capture group — the portion of `«SA_EMAIL»` between `${RBCC_account_director}-` and `@${RBGD_SA_EMAIL_FULL}`
... {rbbc_call}
{buf_write_fact_multi}
with three positional arguments:
.... `<file_root>`: `«IDENTITY»` (bare identity — the basename root for the emitted fact file)
.... `<ext>`: `RBCC_fact_ext_roster_director` (resolves at source time to `roster-director`)
.... `<value>`: `«SA_EMAIL»` (the full service account email address)

//axhos_step
. *Report count*:
.. {rbbc_show}
total count of emitted director fact files

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution rosters {rbtr_director} service accounts via per-SA fact emission — one `roster-director` fact file per discovered identity, each containing the full SA email as its value.
The operation is read-only; no service accounts are created or modified.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_governor_mantle}

NOTE: This operation creates or replaces a
{rbtr_governor}
within a
{rbtgi_depot}.
If a
